<DATELINE>ALEXANDRIA, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Convicted felon and four-time presidential candidate <PERSON> Lyndon </PERSON> <PERSON> LaRouche </PERSON> announced plans Thursday to run for <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> next year. <PERSON> LaRouche </PERSON>, 65, a <LOCATION> Loudoun </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> resident, wants to represent <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION>'s 10th District, which includes <LOCATION> Arlington </LOCATION>, half of <LOCATION> Fairfax </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Loudoun </LOCATION> counties. After filing his intent to run for <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> with the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Election </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> on June 8, <PERSON> LaRouche </PERSON> became the first Democrat to announce plans to go after incumbent <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> representative <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Wolf </PERSON>'s seat. <PERSON> LaRouche </PERSON> was convicted in January in <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Alexandria </LOCATION> on charges of mail fraud, conspiracy to commit mail fraud and conspiracy to defraud the <ORGANIZATION> Internal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Revenue </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION>. He was sentenced to 15 years and is appealing the conviction. He ran for president as an independent in 1976 and as a Democrat in 1980, 1984 and 1988. Asked whether he could serve his constituents well from jail, <PERSON> LaRouche </PERSON> said `` I think this is a very turbulent period of history. I could pop out of prison just as quick as I popped in.'' <PERSON> LaRouche </PERSON> has maintained since his conviction that his trial was political. <PERSON> LaRouche </PERSON> and his associates were convicted for a scheme in which they used a fundraising operation to solicit `` loans'' from people that they did n't pay back. They failed to report the tr