<HEAD>New AP Correspondent Named for San Diego</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN DIEGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Sedeno </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> correspondent in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Antonio </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, for three years, has been named correspondent in charge of the <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION>'s <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Diego </LOCATION> bureau. The appointment was announced Wednesday by <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> Chief of Bureau <PERSON> Andy </PERSON> <PERSON> Lippman </PERSON>. <PERSON> Sedeno </PERSON>, 27, joined the <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> in 1984 and became <LOCATION> Harlingen </LOCATION> correspondent the following year. He is a native of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angelo </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, and a graduate of <ORGANIZATION> Angelo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Sedeno </PERSON> was a copy editor for the <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angelo </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Standard-Times </LOCATION> before joining the AP.
