<HEAD>Enterprise News Editor Named at AP Washington Bureau</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Wayne </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> has been named news editor for enterprise in the <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> bureau of <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION>. The appointment was announced Wednesday by <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> Chief of Bureau <PERSON> Jon </PERSON> <PERSON> Wolman </PERSON>. <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>, 38, has been the supervisor of the <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION>'s <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> news report for afternoon newspapers. He previously was the <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION>'s news editor in <LOCATION> Charleston </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> W. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>, and correspondent in <LOCATION> Montpelier </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Vt. </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> will coordinate enterprise coverage from the nation's capital, including direction of <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION>'s special assignment He also will direct planning for the afternoon news report. A second <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> news editor, <PERSON> Carole </PERSON> <PERSON> Feldman </PERSON>, handles the bureau's coverage of breaking news. <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> is a native of <LOCATION> Dayton </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>, and a graduate of <ORGANIZATION> Dartmouth </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> College </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION>. He joined the <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Montpelier </LOCATION> in 1978 after working for the <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> -LRB- <LOCATION> N.H. </LOCATION> -RRB- Valley News.
