<TEXT>
 Firefighters sweating in 118-degree temperatures Wednesday contained a 935-acre wildfire that briefly threatened a national park. Residents in 85 homes were advised to evacuate at the height of the fire near <ORGANIZATION> Joshua </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tree </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Monument </ORGANIZATION>, which is dedicated to preservation of the gnarled desert trees, but only one building was destroyed. `` The residents had cleared the brush around their homes and if it had n't been for that clearance the homes would definitely have burned,'' said <PERSON> Deborah </PERSON> <PERSON> McClellan </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Forestry </ORGANIZATION>. Temperatures reached above 100 inland and into the high 80s and 90-degree mark elsewhere, and gusty <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ana </LOCATION> winds hampered firefighters as they fought several other brush fires. Fire blackened 175 acres in the hills of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Clemente </LOCATION> in southern <LOCATION> Orange </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> and 35 acres in <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Clarita </LOCATION> in northwestern <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>. Firefighters earlier doused a 300-acre blaze in <LOCATION> Ventura </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> and a 115-acre fire in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bernardino </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> Northern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> was also subject to the same hot, gusty winds and low humidity which helped fan 2,600-acre wildfire 50 miles northeast of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION>. Heavy smoke from the grass fire forced closure of a 10-mile stretch of state Highway 12, authorities said. State R