orld leaders have visited <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION> since the Islamic Revolution in 1979 sent mobs into the streets shouting, `` Death to <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>, Death to <LOCATION> Russia </LOCATION>!'' The <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> was the chief arms supplier to <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> during its long war with <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> that ended in a cease-fire last August. <PERSON> Rafsanjani </PERSON> emphasized in remarks distributed by <ORGANIZATION> Tass </ORGANIZATION> on Wednesday that several months before his death on June 3, <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON> called for better relations with the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Tass </ORGANIZATION> said <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> and <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON> exchanged messages in February, and since then their foreign ministers have met four times. The <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> has about 50 million Moslems, most of them living in rapidly growing Central <LOCATION> Asia </LOCATION>, which borders <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Afghanistan </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>. The <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> has been troubled in the past year and a half by outbreaks of unrest among its more than 100 ethnic groups, and the disturbances have spread in the last six weeks to <LOCATION> Central </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Asia </LOCATION>. About 100 people were killed in rioting in the <LOCATION> Fergana </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION> of eastern <LOCATION> Uzbekistan </LOCATION> earlier this month.
