<BYLINE>By ALEX EFTY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Greece </LOCATION>'s conservative party leader today demanded that interim Premier <PERSON> Andreas </PERSON> <PERSON> Papandreou </PERSON> resign immediately following reports of a new financial scandal linked to his socialist administration. Banner front-page headlines today in the <LOCATION> Athens </LOCATION> press said the scandal involved the laundering of $ 700 million through the <ORGANIZATION> Greek </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mortgage </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Atlantic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION>, a subsidiary of the state-run <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Greece </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Constantine </PERSON> <PERSON> Mitsotakis </PERSON>, leader of the New Democracy party, and opposition dailies blamed <PERSON> Papandreou </PERSON> because the <ORGANIZATION> Mortgage </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> is a state institution and its ranking executives are government appointees. `` We have this new terrible scandal, and this usurper of authority who shames and robs the <LOCATION> Greek </LOCATION> people must leave immediately,'' <PERSON> Mitsotakis </PERSON> said at a news conference. The governor of the <ORGANIZATION> Mortgage </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Giorgos </PERSON> <PERSON> Anomeritis </PERSON>, denied that branches of the bank in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> had committed any wrongdoing. `` Our branches are not allowed by law to accept deposits and consequently they use other American commercial banks. Therefore, they can not be responsible either for illegal desposits or the illegal transfer of funds,'' <PERSON> Anomeritis </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Papandreou </PERSON>'s <ORGANIZ