<DATELINE>ARNHEM, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An army officer was killed today in a highway shootout between a man who kidnapped him and law enforcement officers, police said. It was not immediately clear who shot Col. <PERSON> Karel </PERSON> <PERSON> van </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Kieft </PERSON>, who was kidnapped at gunpoint as he left for work at about 6:45 a.m. Police spokesman <PERSON> Bert </PERSON> <PERSON> Albers </PERSON> said the kidnapper was identified as <PERSON> Stefan </PERSON> <PERSON> Kroger </PERSON>, a 33-year-old from <LOCATION> Hanover </LOCATION>, in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>. In <LOCATION> Hanover </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Hartmut </PERSON> <PERSON> Mollring </PERSON> said that <ORGANIZATION> Kroger </ORGANIZATION> was serving a five-year jail term in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> for several armed robberies and had been at large since May 10 when he failed to show up after a one-day prison furlough. <PERSON> Albers </PERSON> said the kidnapper forced <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Kieft </PERSON>, 56, into his car at gunpoint near the victim's home in <LOCATION> Apeldoorn </LOCATION>, 10 miles north of the eastern city of <LOCATION> Arnhem </LOCATION>. Police, alerted by a neighbor, chased the car and caught up with it at a gas station on the Arnhem-Utrecht freeway, said <PERSON> Albers </PERSON>. Police fired at the kidnapper, who was in the car with his victim, and a shootout ensued in which <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Kieft </PERSON> was killed, <PERSON> Albers </PERSON> said. The motive of the kidnapping was unclear, although at one point the kidnapper demanded $ 450,000 ransom, according to <PERSON> Albers </PERSON>. He said the victim and the kidnapper were apparently not acquainted. <PERSON> Kroger </PERSON> told police he was wanted by West German and Swiss police in connection with several armed robberies, according to <PERSON> Albers </PERSON>. <PERSON> Albers </PERSON> said it was unclear whether <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Kieft </PERSON> was hit by the kidnapper or by police.
