<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A congress of 81 Western socialist parties said Thursday it deplored the `` bloody repression'' in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> Belgium </LOCATION> protested by banning all official visits and by suspending a loan. The <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> roundly attacked the executions in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>, and <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION>'s parliament said that death does not block ideas In <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> Majority Leader <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Mitchell </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Maine </LOCATION>, urged President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> to condemn the executions in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> more forcefully. Secretary of State <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> <PERSON> III </PERSON> asked <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>, however, to mute criticism of administration reaction, saying the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> must `` speak with one voice.'' Chinese authorities executed seven more people on Thursday, bringing to 27 the number reported put to death in two days. Others have been sentenced to die on charges they led student protests for democratic reform in April and May. Condemnation from the <ORGANIZATION> Socialist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> came at the end of its three-day congress in <LOCATION> Stockholm </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Sweden </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> has said it acted to suppress efforts to overthrow its socialist system. <LOCATION> Belgium </LOCATION> banned all official visits to and from <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>, barred new Belgian-Chinese projects and suspended a $ 7.3 million loan because of <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>'s `` flagrant violation of human rights,'' Foreign Affairs Minister <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Eyskens </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Eyskens </PERSON> summoned Chinese Ambassador <PERSON> Liu </PERSON> <PERSON> S