PERSON> Aquino </PERSON> expressed sadness over executions in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>, but `` conceded that the matter is within the domestic jurisdiction of <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>'s courts,'' a statement in <LOCATION> Manila </LOCATION> said. British Prime Minister <PERSON> Margaret </PERSON> <PERSON> Thatcher </PERSON> said Thursday she would not consider economic sanctions against <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>, adding that to do so might prove dangerous to <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s subjects in <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION>. On Wednesday she said she was `` utterly appalled'' by the executions. <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> has canceled ministerial visits to <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> and suspended talks on a new constitution for its colony of <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION> after 1997, when it reverts to <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>. In <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Joachim </PERSON> <PERSON> Herrmann </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Communist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>'s policy-making <PERSON> Politburo </PERSON> said the government published all official Chinese statements with the purpose of denying `` Western horror stories'' and to present `` objective information. In a speech distributed by the state-run news agency <ORGANIZATION> ADN </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Herrmann </PERSON> said the `` peaceful student demonstrations'' in <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> were to be used for a `` counterrevolutionary overthrow of people's power in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>.
