<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A fuel truck spill forced President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> to change his route out of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> Thursday night. Air Force One flew from <LOCATION> Newark </LOCATION> <LOCATION> International </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> John </LOCATION> <LOCATION> F. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kennedy </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Queens </LOCATION> borough of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> because of concerns by security officials about the accident near the <LOCATION> Newark </LOCATION> airport, <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Marlin </PERSON> <PERSON> Fitzwater </PERSON> told reporters. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> delayed the departure of his motorcade from a banquet in downtown <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION> to let <ORGANIZATION> Secret </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> escorts and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> police chart a new course to the <LOCATION> Kennedy </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION>. `` There has been an accident involving two fuel trucks near the <LOCATION> Newark </LOCATION> airport, `` <PERSON> Fitzwater </PERSON> told reporters outside the building where the president and Mrs. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> had attended the 100th anniversary dinner of the Wall Street Journal. <PERSON> Fitzwater </PERSON> said he was not sure what the trucks carried but `` whatever they are they are considered toxic, especially when considered mixed.'' `` For those reasons we have been advised to move <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> One and the press plane to another location,'' he added. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> had flown to <LOCATION> Newark </LOCATION> on Air Force One Thursday morning to visit a she