<BYLINE>By TOM WELLS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A congressman said Thursday that death squads, possibly hired by drug traffickers, are hunting down members of the governing <ORGANIZATION> Liberal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>. Rep. <PERSON> Jorge </PERSON> <PERSON> Infante </PERSON> <PERSON> Leal </PERSON> said in a communique sent to <ORGANIZATION> Liberal </ORGANIZATION> leaders that more than 100 members were killed in the eastern plains in the last year. The <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> confirmed his statements. The ministry said previously that guerrillas of the <ORGANIZATION> Colombian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Revolutionary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Armed </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Forces </ORGANIZATION> are targeting <ORGANIZATION> Liberal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> members. The guerrillas may be taking revenge for right-wing death squads killing more than 800 members of <LOCATION> Colombia </LOCATION>'s biggest leftist party, the <ORGANIZATION> Patriotic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION>, in four years. But <ORGANIZATION> El </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tiempo </ORGANIZATION> newspaper quoted the congressman as saying he is not entirely convinced that guerrillas are behind the killings of <ORGANIZATION> Liberal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> members. <PERSON> Infante </PERSON> <PERSON> Leal </PERSON> said the gunmen could be hired by drug traffickers who are killing Liberals because a <ORGANIZATION> Liberal </ORGANIZATION> faction has sought an alliance with the <ORGANIZATION> Patriotic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION>. Drug runners have been at war with guerrillas here for years because of rebel attempts to kidnap drug traffickers or members of their families and hold them for ransom. Also, drug traffickers resent guerrilla demands of payment of a so-called revolution tax in areas where traffickers raise coca plants for producing