<HEAD>Dollar Down, Gold Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> dollar fell in early trading today against all European currencies and the Japanese yen. Gold prices were higher, moving up on the dollar's weakness. Traders said they were puzzled by the dollar's direction. `` We're all trying to determine what kind of consolidation phase this is. It does n't fit any of the patterns,'' said one analyst in <LOCATION> Milan </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION>. `` Frequent reversals and sharp rallies are both possible,'' said another analyst in <LOCATION> Milan </LOCATION>. In <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION>, where trading ends before the European markets open, the dollar closed at 141.40, down 3.55 yen from Wednesday's close. Later in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, it was trading at 140.75 yen. Other late rates for the dollar in <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>, compared with Wednesday's late rates, included: 1.9525 West German marks, down from 1.9680; 1.6830 Swiss francs, down from 1.7005; 6.6250 French francs, down from 6.6795; 2.2002 Dutch guilders, down from 2.2375; 1,418.55 Italian lire, down from 1.439.50; and 1.1920 Canadian dollars, down from 1.19675. In <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, one British pound cost $ 1.5615, compared with $ 1.54675 late Wednesday. Gold opened in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> at $ 370.70 an ounce, up from $ 366.75 late Wednesday. At mid-morning, the city's five major gold dealers fixed a recommended price of $ 370.40. In <LOCATION> Zurich </LOCATION>, gold was selling at $ 370 this morning, up from $ 366.40 late Wednesday. Earlier in <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION> gold closed at $ 370.49, up from $ 366.57 late Wednesday. Gold moved up $ 5.75 in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> trading on Wednesday following a late rally on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commodity </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> that pushed the price as high as $ 372.40. Deal