ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION> $ 95.3 million more a year for represented employees alone by the end of the contract. That's $ 7.5 million more than we made in 1988, and 1988 was the most profitable year for <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION> since 1979,'' he said. National rebutted complaints that <ORGANIZATION> USW </ORGANIZATION> members got more money in the early stages of their 50-month contract with <ORGANIZATION> Bethelehem </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> `` They gave up more in 1986, and they are catching up to you now,'' <PERSON> Coffee </PERSON> said. Like the <LOCATION> Bethlehem </LOCATION> agreement ratified recently by union members, the National offer would have restored past concessions and raised hourly wages by $ 1.50 over the contract term.
