ks up. But the DOE report released late Wednesday showed that total gasoline supplies were down 1.3 million barrels to 218.7 million barrels. `` The new numbers were surprising because usually the two reports are pretty close,'' said <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Baker </PERSON>, analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Prudential-Bache </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> `` It was a factor that affected prices.'' Both reports showed a decline in crude and heating oil inventories for the week and a drop of some 30 million barrels in total oil supplies, including crude and products, from last year.
