 A 3 percent raise for <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Auto </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Workers </ORGANIZATION> union President <PERSON> Owen </PERSON> <PERSON> Bieber </PERSON> and the union's other top officers was approved Thursday by delegates to the union's constitutional convention. The raise, retroactive to June 1, boosted <PERSON> Bieber </PERSON>'s annual salary as head of the 1 million-member union to $ 91,469.42. <PERSON> Bieber </PERSON> and the other officers also will receive quarterly cost-of-living adjustments and 3 percent lump-sum payments on June 1, 1990 and on the same day in 1991. For <PERSON> Bieber </PERSON>, each lump-sum payment works out to at least $ 2,744.08. The formula of a 3 percent raise, COLA adjustments and lump-sum payments for the union's 21 top officers is the same as that negotiated for <ORGANIZATION> UAW </ORGANIZATION> members in 1987 at <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. Last year, the <ORGANIZATION> UAW </ORGANIZATION> negotiated a contract with <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> calling for two 3 percent lump sum payments that brought wages for all Big Three workers into balance <ORGANIZATION> UAW </ORGANIZATION> Secretary-Treasurer <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Casstevens </PERSON>' salary went to $ 83,078.35 with two annual lump-sum payments of at least $ 2,492.35. Salaries for vice presidents <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> Yokich </PERSON>, <PERSON> Ernie </PERSON> <PERSON> Lofton </PERSON>, <PERSON> Stan </PERSON> <PERSON> Marshall </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Odessa </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kommer </ORGANIZATION> rose to $ 79,800.56 a year, plus two annual payments of at least $ 2,394.02. Pay for the union's 15 regional directors rose to $ 71,409.48 wi